title: I Have a Bed Made of Buttermilk Pancakes by Jaclyn Moriarty (ret
description: Cath Murphy, second-grade teacher, was feeling awkward and foolish, but she also felt this: quirky, cocky, small, funny, wicked and extremely blonde. As her mother liked to say, all meetings with new people, even locksmiths or seven-year-olds, can make you a little afraid.
